                <div type="section" xml:id="DISCUSSION">
                    <head type="section">Discussion</head>
                    <p>Two patriotic images related to Trafalgar hung in the dining room of <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s paternal grandparents, when they lived 
                        in <placeName type="building" corresp="#STJAMESSQEDINBURGH">St. James Square</placeName> in <placeName type="building" corresp="#NEWTOWNEDINBURGH">New Town</placeName> of <placeName corresp="#EDINBURGH">Edinburgh</placeName>. 
                        One was a picture of Captain George Duff, killed at Trafalgar in 1805, which 
                        <persName corresp="#VAB">Van Akin Burd</persName> suggests may have been an engraving by George Dawe after a portrait by Henry Raeburn. 
                        Two other pictures depicted Nelson (<title type="letter" corresp="ctwr_to_jjr_1807-11-02"><persName corresp="#CTWR">Catherine Ruskin</persName> to <persName corresp="#JJR">John James Ruskin</persName>, <date when="1807-11-02">2 November 1807</date></title>, 
                        in <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#RFL"><persName corresp="#VAB">Burd</persName> ed., <title type="book" corresp="#RFL"><hi rend="italic">Ruskin Family Letters</hi></title></ref>, 1:12, 14 n. 3).</p>
                </div>
